				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Ten Summoner's Tales<a name="47215"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 20 04 8:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm wondering if anyone has a guide or link or list of places where creatures are of level 58-65 and don't summon (or of ones that do summon to help the process of elimination).
<br />

<br />
Some NPCs that do and don't summon:
<br />

<br />
1- Plane of Mischief :- Majority of NPCs in the entry area are swarm kitable, giving about 1.7-1.9% per mob to a vah shir bard.
<br />

<br />
2- Plane of Mischief :- Irritating Mushroom, Funky Skunk, Bzzbiana and one of the mushroom men on the far right hand side; these all summon. Personally I keep tried to charm them, and set them on a very large pull in the hopes they'll die. Funky Skunk is very likely to break charm. I leave them alone now.
<br />

<br />
3- Plane of Nightmare - Gnarled Treants, Blood Ravens, Small Bats, Virulent Arachnids and Hatchlings, Small Bat, Werewolves and Hobgoblins don't summon.
<br />

<br />
4- Maiden's Eye - There is an area of umbral toilers near the lake in the top left corner. The spawn rate is insane, and you can go thru a bar of mana in very little time. However the exp makes it of dubious worth.
<br />

<br />
5- Umbral Plains - Full of summoners. Ouch.
<br />

<br />
6- Nadox - Kiting here can be tricky because its indoors, but with RS3 you'll do OK but will want to use an external view. A good place to solo for cash-in-and drops. Some of the luggards are uncharmable even with the 64 song.
<br />

<br />
7- Natimbi - The mobs are moderate exp and don't summon. You will, unfortunately, find yourself continually &quot;unable to see %t from here&quot; and taking damage from falls. Not a great place for bard kiting<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
8- Qinmi - There are several swarm kitable spawns here, but you have to watch for the odd npc that summons; I haven't yet started making a list.
<br />

<br />
9- Ferubi - This zone seemed to start out as great exp and light on summoners; unfortunately I got close enough to or train-agrod a named and was returning to home point before I knew anything was amiss. There is a blocked zone exit in the top right, which if unoccupied is just right for a bard to aoe or swarm kite in with a good degree of control.
<br />

<br />
10- Plane of Disease - most of the yard trash here doesn't summon; but the loot bites and the exp isn't up to PoN. Adds are plentiful tho, so the stream of exp is easier to maintain.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
