				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm one of those people to whom charm kiting comes naturally, and when I found Bzzbiana in PoM was a summoner, I instinctively charmed *her* and burned her. But I'm not finding it to be a particularly useful technique. By and large the only times I ever die when charm kiting are:
<br />
- When I try it in a GoD zone (the first thing to cast or agro on me usually instantly wipes me out)
<br />
- When I make the mistake of tagging 3+ casters (so I can't fade)
<br />
- When I try to charm burn
<br />

<br />
A question to my fellow charm-kiters. Have you noticed that in PoP zones mobs seem to have a long delay after their initial round of attack? If I'm CKing and something goes wrong, and mobs manage to hit me, naturally I get stunned, but stun actually wears off and I start moving well before the mobs try to hit me again. How long has that been like that?
<br />
</span></td>
